SUMMARY — HOW TO IDENTIFY BACKTRACKING PROBLEMS

  Signal in problem          What to do
  --------------------       ------------------------------
  "all possible..."          Backtracking
  "all subsets/combinations" Use take/skip or for loop
  "all permutations"         Use used[] array
  "all valid placements"     Use constraint checks (N-Queens)
  "sum equals target"        Pass remaining = target - num
  "can reuse elements"       Stay at i (not i+1)
  "no reuse"                 Move to i+1
--------------------------------------------------------------
THE THREE STEPS — ALWAYS
  CHOOSE    → add to path / mark used / place on board
  EXPLORE   → call backtrack recursively
  UNDO      → remove from path / mark unused / remove from board
--------------------------------------------------------------
